-- Biomet names Binder CEO
-- 
-- Mon Feb 26, 2007 9:33am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/26/us-biomet-ceo-idUSWNAS206920070226

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Orthopedic device maker Biomet Inc. BMET.O, which plans to be acquired by a group of private equity firms for about $10.9 billion, on Tuesday said it named Jeffrey Binder, 43, president and chief executive. 


 Binder replaces Daniel Hann, who has served as interim president and chief executive since Dane Miller retired last March. Binder most recently served in senior management roles at Abbott Laboratories Inc. ( ABT.N ). Hann will remain as an executive vice president and board member. The appointment is effective immediately.